# UI elements and CSS

Before changing templates or stylesheets, read [docs/UI-Elements.md](../../docs/UI-Elements.md).

## Stylesheet bundles

| File | Put styles here when |
|------|----------------------|
| `style/main.css` | Global shell, public reading, shared primitives (`.btn`, `.form-group`, `.container`) |
| `style/manage.css` | Profile, dashboard, library, review, CRUD lists, notifications, subscriptions |
| `style/write.css` | Write editor only |
| `style/fonts.css` | `@font-face` only |

Load order in `components/head.html`: fonts → main → manage → write → third-party.

## Class names

- BEM: `block`, `block__element`, `block--modifier`; utilities `u-*`.
- **Do not** add new CSS classes without registering the block in UI-Elements.md.
- User-visible strings: [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) UI labels table.

## Buttons

Always `class="btn btn--…"`. Use documented modifiers only (`--primary`, `--secondary`, `--outline`, `--small`, etc.). Never `btn--sm` — use `btn--small`.

## Lists

Reading → Load more (`contraponto-pagination.mdc`). Managing → `manage-pagination` partial.

## New surfaces

1. Register block in UI-Elements.md.
2. Add CSS to the correct bundle.
3. Update UI-Guidelines.md for UX narrative if it is a new page type.
